{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4721ff54-d86b-41c6-9b45-b2b0c56f64fb","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but it depends on `Domain.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_OR5JaiPZUFYTV8zbWlxnFE","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-30e7f6f5500a42da8b800107aee9916f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-30e7f6f5500a42da8b800107aee9916f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"51222d24-ea74-4e02-b35d-1d52f68c6967","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), and `Program.fs` depends on both. So `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n\n\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"2827:2657C1:1BA27C6:1EAD08F:69FA8F7A"},"id":"60332f3f-4ea6-414a-9469-1cbab479aee0","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:46:58.703Z","parentId":"08407b2d-62a3-4c99-bf75-3bba11eb8342"}
